@Sherlockyyf I just checked the pre-trained weights on PyTorch `1.0.1.post2` on both Python 3.6 and Anaconda environments. The only time this error occurs is with earlier versions of PyTorch since they have changed the implementation of `spectral_norm` layer in PyTorch `1.0`. Can you create a new python environment and install PyTorch `1.0.1` and test again?

@levi0809 Her error is in train mode, while yours is in test mode. Can you please verify that you are using PyTorch version `1.0.1` and able to train the edge mode:
```
python train.py --model 1 --checkpoints ./checkpoints/celeba
```
